<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF82FFFE39D30F844355BD1B" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" type="description">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF82FFFE39D30F844335BD3F" blockId="12.[136,1452,1202,2093]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE39D30F8447E6BFE3" bold="true" box="[136,200,1202,1228]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Trees</emphasis>
2.5–6(–10) m tall, rhytidome thick, grooved, slightly suberous; 1 pair of nectaries present on the branch right below the insertion of the petiole (a nectary at each side), slightly verruciform to depressed. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3DE00FE04223BFDF" bold="true" box="[1211,1293,1238,1264]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Leaves</emphasis>
with (2–)3–4 pair of pinnae, opposite to subopposite; 3–5(–7) pairs of leaflets, opposite to subopposite; petiolar nectaries absent; leaflets (2–)2.5–5(–9) × (0.2–)1.5–4.5(–6) cm, apex usually round, sometimes slightly emarginate, rarely truncate or asymmetrically round, very rarely acute, margin flat, coriaceous, slightly discolor to discolor, glabrous on both surfaces, very rarely sparsely puberule along the midrib on lower surface, unilateral tuft of trichomes on lower surface absent. Inflorescences of simple thyrsi; cymulae of 3–4(–5) spikes; spike with (9–)10–12(–20) cm long; spike prophylls deciduous, rarely late deciduous, 
<quantity id="640843B7FF82FFFE38A70E984560BEE6" box="[508,590,1454,1481]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" metricValueMax="4.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" unit="cm" value="3.5" valueMax="4.0" valueMin="3.0">3–4 cm</quantity>
long. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3BCF0E9845DDBEE7" bold="true" box="[660,755,1454,1480]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Flowers</emphasis>
monoclinous, whitish to yellowish, anther gland sessile. 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3C360E984285BEE7" bold="true" box="[1389,1451,1454,1480]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Fruit</emphasis>
a nucoid legume, strongly curved to spiral, flat-compressed to subturgid, 8–10 × 1.5–1.8(–3) cm, valves coriaceous to woody, light-brown yellowish and ferruginous-pulverulent, glabrescent (
<figureCitation id="3BCBF2D7FF82FFFE3AED0EC04323BD3F" box="[950,1037,1526,1552]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="7.[136,229,1956,1978]" captionTargetBox="[202,1386,190,1932]" captionTargetId="figure-17@7.[202,1386,190,1932]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURE 1. Tree species of Stryphnodendron. A. Stryphnodendron pulcherrimum (Willd.) Hochr.; B. Stryphnodendron racemiferum (Ducke) W.A.Rodrigues; C. Stryphnodendron coriaceum Benth.; D. Stryphnodendron adstringens (Mart.) Coville; E. Stryphnodendron rotundifolium var. rotundifolium Mart.; F. Stryphnodendron rotundifolium var. villosum (Benth.) Scalon; G. Stryphnodendron roseiflorum (Ducke) Ducke." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6520282" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6520282/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Fig. 1C</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF82FFFE39E60D2C4355BD1B" blockId="12.[136,1452,1202,2093]" box="[189,1147,1562,1589]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE39E60D2C468EBD1B" bold="true" box="[189,416,1562,1588]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Vernacular names:</emphasis>
— 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE38E70D2C456CBD1B" box="[444,578,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Barbatimão</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3B140D2C4411BD1B" box="[591,831,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Barbatimão do Norte</emphasis>
or 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3A3F0D2C4355BD1B" box="[868,1147,1562,1588]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Barbatimão do Cerrado.</emphasis>
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF82FFFE39E60D08437DBC23" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF82FFFE39E60D08437DBC23" blockId="12.[136,1452,1202,2093]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE39E60D084690BD77" bold="true" box="[189,446,1598,1624]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Nomenclatural notes:</emphasis>
— 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF82FFFE38810D0845BEBD76" author="Bentham, G." box="[474,656,1598,1625]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" pagination="335 - 375" refId="ref41649" refString="Bentham, G. (1875) Revision of the suborder Mimoseae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London 30 (3): 335 - 375. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1875. tb 00005. x" type="journal article" year="1875">Bentham (1875)</bibRefCitation>
referred as type of 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF82FFFE3A3D0D0944D9BD77" authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1875" box="[870,1015,1599,1625]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coriaceum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3A3D0D0944D9BD77" box="[870,1015,1599,1625]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">S. coriaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at least 
<specimenCount id="B5F625DBFF82FFFE3D0A0D0943C9BD76" box="[1105,1255,1599,1625]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" type="generic" typeStatus="syntypes">two syntypes</specimenCount>
, indicated merely by their collection sites (
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE38FC0D5446C4BD53" box="[423,490,1634,1660]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Bahia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE3B7D0D544591BD53" box="[550,703,1634,1660]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
states in 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FF82FFFE3A6A0D544454BD52" box="[817,890,1634,1661]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Brazil</collectingCountry>
). The author’s comments in this work (
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF82FFFE3C1F0D5447EFBD8E" author="Bentham, G." pageId="12" pageNumber="239" pagination="335 - 375" refId="ref41649" refString="Bentham, G. (1875) Revision of the suborder Mimoseae. Transactions of the Linnean Society of London 30 (3): 335 - 375. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1096 - 3642.1875. tb 00005. x" type="journal article" year="1875">Bentham 1875</bibRefCitation>
) suggest that it was written simultaneously with 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF82FFFE3B850DB0448ABD8F" baseAuthorityName="Bentham" baseAuthorityYear="1876" box="[734,932,1670,1696]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Flora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3B850DB0448ABD8F" box="[734,932,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Flora brasiliensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and that the latter was expected to be released first, but it was published only in the following year. In 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF82FFFE3A590D9C43BFBDEA" authority=", Bentham (1876)" authorityName=", Bentham" authorityYear="1876" box="[770,1169,1706,1733]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Flora" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3A590D9C44E5BDEB" box="[770,971,1706,1732]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Flora brasiliensis</emphasis>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="C76193A3FF82FFFE3A810D9C43BFBDEA" author="Bentham, G." box="[986,1169,1706,1733]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" pagination="257 - 502" refId="ref41697" refString="Bentham, G. (1876) Leguminosae II et III. Mimoseae. In: Martius, C. F. P. (Ed.) Flora brasiliensis. v. 15, pars 2. Lipsiae apud Frid. Fleishcer in Comm., Monachii, pp. 257 - 502." type="book chapter" year="1876">Bentham (1876)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
provides more details of the types mentioned in his 1875 work, allowing the association of 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3ADD0DF94321BDC7" box="[902,1039,1743,1768]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Martius s.n.</emphasis>
and 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3D110DF943CDBDC7" box="[1098,1251,1742,1768]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Martius 1820</emphasis>
to the specimens collected in 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE384A0DC4467CBC23" box="[273,338,1778,1804]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Bahia</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE38D20DC4450CBC23" box="[393,546,1778,1804]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
, respectively. The latter was selected as 
<typeStatus id="7C4B50F0FF82FFFE3ABE0DC44361BC23" box="[997,1103,1778,1804]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">lectotype</typeStatus>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EBEABDD9FF82FFFF39E60C20435BBB96" lastPageId="13" lastPageNumber="240" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="A34FEE52FF82FFFE39E60C204548B303" blockId="12.[136,1452,1202,2093]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE39E60C2046C0BC1F" bold="true" box="[189,494,1814,1840]" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Distribution and habitat:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName id="64F095D1FF82FFFE3B510C204464BC1F" authorityName="Bentham" authorityYear="1875" box="[522,842,1814,1840]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Stryphnodendron" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="12" pageNumber="239" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="coriaceum">
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3B510C204464BC1F" box="[522,842,1814,1840]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Stryphnodendron coriaceum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in areas of low rainfall and commonly grows on sandy soils, mainly in campo-cerrado, cerrado, cerradão, tabuleiro or caatinga from Northeastern 
<collectingCountry id="DBE7AEC2FF82FFFE3C480C0C4279BC7B" box="[1299,1367,1850,1876]" name="Brazil" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE3C320C0C4289BC7B" box="[1385,1447,1850,1876]" country="Brazil" name="Piaui" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Piauí</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE39D30C6847D2BC57" box="[136,252,1886,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE38500C684662BC57" box="[267,332,1886,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Ceará</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE38D20C6846E4BC57" box="[393,458,1886,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Bahia</collectingRegion>
states), Central-Western (states of 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE3A3A0C68448CBC57" box="[865,930,1886,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Goiás</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE3A850C684363BC57" box="[990,1101,1886,1912]" country="Brazil" name="Tocantins" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Tocantins</collectingRegion>
, in the region of Jalapão) and Northern 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE39AE0CB446A3BCB3" box="[245,397,1922,1948]" country="Brazil" name="Minas Gerais" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Minas Gerais</collectingRegion>
adjacent to 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE3B420CB44574BCB3" box="[537,602,1922,1948]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Bahia</collectingRegion>
(Serra da Capivara) and 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE3A220CB44494BCB3" box="[889,954,1922,1948]" country="Brazil" name="Goias" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Goiás</collectingRegion>
states. The sample 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3DC00CB54201BCB3" box="[1179,1327,1922,1949]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Sampaio 206</emphasis>
is referred to occur in restinga vegetation (
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE38B20C90451EBCEF" box="[489,560,1958,1984]" country="Brazil" name="Ceara" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Ceará</collectingRegion>
), but was collected in a Botanical Garden and there is no information whether it is a natural or cultivated occurrence. The reference of this species to Pará state refers to a cultivated tree grown from seeds collected in campos cerrados in 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE3B6D0CD84584B327" box="[566,682,2030,2056]" country="Brazil" name="Maranhao" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Maranhão</collectingRegion>
, and Glaziou´s record in 
<collectingRegion id="613420B0FF82FFFE3A9E0CD84346B327" box="[965,1128,2030,2056]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
(São João da Barra, 
<emphasis id="91843240FF82FFFE3C080CD847EEB303" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="239">Glaziou 9753</emphasis>
at P) is uncertain but highly unlikely.
</paragraph>
